Speaker.create(name: "Cate Huston", twitter: "catehstn", announced: false, photo: "cate.jpg", bio: "Cate Huston is a developer and entrepreneur focused on mobile. Sheâ€™s lived and worked in the UK, Australia, Canada, China and the United States, as an engineer at Google, an Extreme Blue intern at IBM, and a ski instructor. Cate speaks internationally on mobile development and her writing has been published on sites as varied as Lifehacker, The Daily Beast, The Eloquent Woman and Model View Culture. She co-curates Technically Speaking, blogs at Accidentally in Code and is @catehstn on Twitter.", bio_ja: "Cate Huston is a developer and entrepreneur focused on mobile. Sheâ€™s lived and worked in the UK, Australia, Canada, China and the United States, as an engineer at Google, an Extreme Blue intern at IBM, and a ski instructor. Cate speaks internationally on mobile development and her writing has been published on sites as varied as Lifehacker, The Daily Beast, The Eloquent Woman and Model View Culture. She co-curates Technically Speaking, blogs at Accidentally in Code and is @catehstn on Twitter.")
